# MCP Server Development

## SDK Registration

Tools are registered with the MCP SDK via `server.tool()`. The SDK expects `tool.inputSchema.shape` (the raw Zod shape object), not the full ZodObject. The ToolDefinition type enforces `z.ZodObject<z.ZodRawShape>` for this reason.

## Bridge

ExtensionBridge is the WebSocket server that talks to the Chrome extension.

- `start()` returns a Promise that resolves when the server is listening (needed for test synchronization)
- `callTool(name, params)` sends a request and waits for a matching response by ID
- Requests have per-tool timeouts defined in TOOL_TIMEOUTS (5s clicks, 60s navigation, etc.)
- Failed requests retry up to maxRetries (default 2) before throwing
- `waitForConnection(timeoutMs)` blocks until an extension connects or times out

## Error Handling

Tool handlers in index.ts are wrapped in try/catch. Errors return MCP-formatted error responses (isError: true) rather than crashing the server. The bridge also handles WebSocket-level errors (connection drops, timeouts) separately from tool-level errors.

## CLI Setup Flag

`mcp-server/src/index.ts` checks for `--setup` in argv before importing the MCP SDK. If present, it runs `agent-config/setup.mjs` and exits. This lets `npx real-browser-mcp --setup cursor` work as a one-liner.
